        "local_audio_uri": "file:///var/mobile/Containers/Data/Application/171121ED-FC13-410A-8985-271D6F0AC7D8/Documents/audio/recording_1767848477106_im1l6t8etwmk4zc71u.m4a",
        "transcript_text": "The painters used a projective covering which left a residue on the north side of the building on the exterior metal panels. This residue would not be cleaned off by regular alcohol because that would damage the panels, so we needed to use a product called Oil Flow. So in the future, if this ever happens, we should be using the specific product or reading the manual for the metal panels.",
